UPDATE public.designers
SET biography = $$Born in The Potteries, Staffordshire, to an Anglo-Swiss father and a Brazilian mother, HAMREI honed his eye for design between the British countryside and summers in the Mediterranean. After studying Architecture, he pivoted to interiors and furniture under the formative guidance of Gisbert Pöppler in Berlin, then deepened his sensibility for materials and colour during three years with Peter Mikic in London.

He went on to join French designer Pierre Yovanovitch, managing interior projects across the United States and the United Kingdom while quietly releasing his first independent furniture pieces. In the summer of 2021 he founded his own studio, today based in the art district of Lisbon — an industrial former nightclub, DAM, that doubles as an appointment-only showroom and event space.

With a team across London and Lisbon, HAMREI co-creates contemporary handmade furniture and objects with European artisanal workshops, sitting deliberately at the edge of art and function. His signature has been described as "a base of beautiful brutalism softened with light-hearted playfulness" — sculptural, architectural lines tempered by warmth, colour and the considered interaction of textures.

Sustainability is intrinsic to the practice rather than decorative: materials are sourced locally where possible, toxic and non-recyclable substances avoided, and craftspeople chosen for their eco-conscious and animal-welfare awareness alongside the highest standards of making. Design to Society profiles him as "a British-Brazilian artist and designer driven by a vision of creating sustainable luxury," while The London List has placed him under the headline "Innovative Simplicity."

"My main ambition is to build a successful studio that stays true to its creative values while pushing the boundaries of sustainable luxury design," he has said — a quiet manifesto for a maker more interested in longevity than in fast fashion.$$,
    updated_at = now()
WHERE name ILIKE 'hamrei';